# UI specifications

When working on console UI (header, modals, main view, layout, or any on-screen content):

1. **Read the format**: Follow [docs/ui-spec-format.md](docs/ui-spec-format.md) for the structure of UI spec documents (screenshot block + line reference).
2. **Read UI components**: Use [docs/ui-components.md](docs/ui-components.md) to understand which component is responsible for each part of the screen (title bar, header, modals, toolbar, visualizer area).
3. **Read existing specs**: When changing an existing screen, read the corresponding UI spec in `docs/` (e.g. `docs/ui-spec-main-view-example.md`) so line numbers and descriptions stay accurate.
4. **Update or create specs when you change layout**:
   - If you add, remove, or reorder lines in a documented screen, update that spec: refresh the screenshot (from a screen dump per ADR-0046) and update the "Line reference" section so every line is listed and described.
   - If you add a new screen or modal that should be documented, create a new UI spec file in `docs/` following the format (screenshot + line reference); optionally add a short index or link from README or other docs.
5. **Generating screenshots**: Use the app’s screen dump (Print Screen or `--dump-after N` / `--dump-path`) to capture ASCII output; paste into the Screenshot block and then write the line reference for each line.

Do not complete console UI changes that affect what appears on screen without updating the relevant UI spec so the docs stay in sync with the implementation.
